  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Safety Coordinator",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description</strong><br /><br /><strong>1. Safety Planning & Compliance</strong></p><ul><li><p>Implement the <strong>Project HSE Plan</strong> for tunnelling works</p></li><li><p>Ensure compliance with <strong>local safety laws, OSHA/ISO standards, and client requirements</strong></p></li><li><p>Review and approve <strong>method statements, risk assessments (JSA/JHA), and permits to work</strong></p></li><li><p>Coordinate safety requirements for <strong>blasting, excavation, shotcreting, and TBM operations</strong></p></li></ul><h3><strong>2. Site Monitoring & Inspections</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Conduct <strong>daily underground safety inspections</strong></p></li><li><p>Monitor critical hazards:</p><ul><li><p>Ground instability & rock falls</p></li><li><p>Ventilation & air quality (gas, dust, oxygen levels)</p></li><li><p>Water ingress & flooding</p></li><li><p>Explosives handling (if applicable)</p></li><li><p>Electrical and heavy machinery risks</p></li></ul></li><li><p>Stop unsafe work and report violations immediately</p></li></ul><h3><strong>3. Training & Awareness</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Deliver <strong>toolbox talks</strong> and safety briefings</p></li><li><p>Conduct <strong>safety inductions</strong> for new workers and visitors</p></li><li><p>Train workers on:</p><ul><li><p>Confined space entry</p></li><li><p>Emergency evacuation</p></li><li><p>PPE usage</p></li><li><p>Working near TBM/blasting zones</p></li></ul></li></ul><h3><strong>4. Incident Management</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Investigate <strong>accidents, near misses, and unsafe conditions</strong></p></li><li><p>Prepare <strong>incident reports and corrective action plans</strong></p></li><li><p>Coordinate with management to prevent recurrence</p></li></ul><h3><strong>5. Emergency Preparedness</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Ensure readiness for <strong>fire, gas leaks, collapse, flooding, and medical emergencies</strong></p></li><li><p>Monitor emergency equipment:</p><ul><li><p>Refuge chambers</p></li><li><p>Gas detectors</p></li><li><p>Firefighting systems</p></li><li><p>Emergency lighting and communication systems</p></li></ul></li><li><p>Participate in <strong>mock drills and emergency response exercises</strong></p></li></ul><h3><strong>6. Documentation & Reporting</strong></h3><p><p>Maintain HSE records:</p><ul><li><p>Inspection reports</p></li><li><p>Training logs</p></li><li><p>Permit-to-work systems</p></li><li><p>Incident statistics</p></li></ul></p><p>Prepare <strong>daily/weekly safety reports</strong> for management and clients<br /><br /><br /><strong>Requirements</strong><br /></p><ul><li>Able to work 6 days per week, including Saturday and Sunday shift work</li></ul><ul><li>Diploma or Degree in <strong>Safety Engineering, Occupational Health & Safety</strong></li></ul><p><ul><li>Valid <strong>Safety Officer certification</strong> </li></ul></p><p><ul><li>5 years experiences in <strong>tunnelling projects</strong></li></ul></p><p><ul><li>Knowledge of <strong>TBM, NATM, drill & blast methods</strong><br /><br /><br /><br /></li></ul></p><p><ul></ul></p>",
